To build:
	cd src; make; cd ..

To test:
	cd test
	../bin/wav_cp sample.wav copy.wav // copies "sample.wav" into "copy.wav"
	../bin/wav_hist sample.wav 0 // outputs the histogram of channel 0 (left)
	../bin/wav_dct sample.wav out.wav // generates a DCT "compressed" version
	

	// exercise 1
	../bin/wav_hist <input file> <channel> <bin>

	// exercise 2
	../bin/wav_quant <input file> <output file> <quantization bits>

	// exercise 3
	../bin/wav_cmp <sample1 file> <sample2 file>


To generate histogram figures (requires gnuplot):
	cd test
	./get_hist_figs.sh <sample.wav>

to generate quantization figures (requires gnuplot):
	cd test
	./get_quant_figs.sh <sample.wav>

To clean up generated files by histogram figures and quantization figures:
	cd test
	./clean.sh	
